A new wind in our sails.

02:10:48.535 --> 02:11:00.200
A new wind in the ministers' sails.

02:11:00.200 --> 02:11:12.317
We pray a new wind in John Kilpatrick's sails.

02:11:12.317 --> 02:11:31.600
We pray a new wind in their sails.

02:11:31.600 --> 02:11:43.720
Right now, these elder men, we call a wind in their sails once again.

02:11:43.720 --> 02:11:44.680
Yeah, Lord.

02:11:44.680 --> 02:11:47.293
He said he's going to lengthen the day.

02:11:56.023 --> 02:11:56.309
Like Joshua, I see the longer day.

02:11:56.309 --> 02:12:04.000
It's like the sun is moving back, but I'm giving you a longer day.

02:12:04.000 --> 02:12:07.209
He wants to bring in the harvest.

02:12:47.930 --> 02:12:49.900
You can see where it was at noon; it's moving back.

02:12:49.900 --> 02:12:54.191
He said, 'Ask me for them.

02:12:54.191 --> 02:13:01.451
In the realm of faith, in that place in the spirit realm, ask me for it.

02:13:01.451 --> 02:13:02.989
What do you believe me for?

02:13:02.989 --> 02:13:06.846
Stretch forth and believe me for more.

02:13:06.846 --> 02:13:15.931
' I hear the Lord say, 'You need to stretch yourself to believe me for more.

02:13:26.360 --> 02:13:26.640
You're believing too small in these last days.

02:13:33.833 --> 02:13:34.240
I am exceedingly abundantly above all that you dare ask or think.

02:13:34.240 --> 02:13:36.954
' Believe me for more.

02:13:39.926 --> 02:13:40.520
Don't settle for anything.

02:13:40.520 --> 02:13:44.450
Believe him for exceedingly abundantly above all that you ask or think.

02:13:44.450 --> 02:13:47.940
I'm not staying at this mealy-mouthed level.

02:13:47.940 --> 02:13:50.667
